# Botho from the Basics — project brief

A ground-up teaching companion to the Botho whitepaper (authored via
`anvil:paper`). The whitepaper is a terse, citable, spec-style document for
cryptographers, auditors, and implementers. This companion teaches the same
primitives — stealth addresses, ring signatures / CLSAG, Pedersen commitments +
Bulletproofs, and the novel-to-Botho pieces (hybrid PQ stealth addresses, the
SCP+PoW split, anti-hoarding demurrage) — to technically-curious
non-cryptographers, building to an end-to-end transaction walkthrough as the
capstone.

## What this primer teaches (and what it defers)

- **Teaches from intuition**: why each mechanism exists, why this design choice,
  what breaks without it — in plain language, with load-bearing analogies,
  before any notation.
- **Defers to the spec**: formal derivations, security proofs, and normative
  parameter tables live in the whitepaper. This companion cross-references them
  ("for the formal treatment, see §X") — it does not restate them.

## Reference material

- `refs/` — diagram sources (mermaid message flows, the transaction walkthrough)
  and any supporting notes.
- The `spec_ref` whitepaper is the consistency oracle: `primer-audit` reads it to
  flag any primer claim that contradicts it; `primer-review` reads it to flag any
  formal section the primer duplicates instead of cross-referencing.
